The paper focuses on using Agent-Based Modeling (ABM) to model and analyze communication aspects of a road traffic management system, which is an example of an Internet of Things (IoT) network. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the categories of Multiagent Systems (cs.MA), Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI), and Systems and Control (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper involves modeling and decision-making, which could fall under the categories of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC).
